- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper's focus on non-monotone interactions and their influence on network behaviour is relevant to the study of neural networks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper's analysis of the diversity and complexity of network behaviours could be relevant to machine learning applications. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper's discussion of convergence speeds in Boolean automata networks could be relevant to the study of control systems.
